---
---

<header
  class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-[var(--b1)] bg-[var(--s1)] px-10 py-12"
>
  <div
    class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.04]"
    style="background-image: linear-gradient(var(--b1) 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, var(--b1) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 40px 40px;"
    aria-hidden="true"
  />
  <div class="relative animate-fade-up">
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[4px] text-[var(--lime)] mb-3">
      // comparison playground
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-[clamp(44px,6vw,80px)] leading-none tracking-tight text-[var(--tx)] mb-3">
      Compare <em class="not-italic text-[var(--lime)]">Head to Head</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="font-mono text-base text-[var(--tx3)] max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      Drag or click two languages to compare scores, practical scenarios, VS Code-style snippets, and runnable demo output.
      JavaScript and TypeScript run in-browser, while other languages show expected output with caveats.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>
